msg: printf() * variable (as in "%.*s") must be int

author: rbb
msg: Quickly parse the libtool.m4 file to use $(apr_builddir) instead
of $(top_builddir).  This allows apr-util to use APR's build directory.

author: rbb
msg: The rules.mk files must use something other than top_builddir.  This is so
that multiple source trees can all use $(top_builddir), and just use
APR's rules.mk file.  Without this, every source tree that uses this
rules.mk file, thinks it's top_builddir is APR's top_builddir.  This ties
in with the next commit to APR-util to make it use APR's build directory.

author: wrowe
msg: Fix a potential source of confusion... any bad filename string is EINVAL
